  "doc_id": "13405",
  "text": "For both FAIR ASST and PICORE sequences (Figure 1 ), a 15.36 ms hyperbolic secant inversion pulse with 22 T RF amplitude and 95% labeling efficiency was used. The slab thickness for the inversion was adjusted by varying the slice-select gradient amplitude based on a reference value of 0.7 mT/m for a 100 mm slab [CITATION_1] . Both sequences incorporated Q2TIPS method to define temporal bolus duration ( 1 ) [CITATION_2] . After a postlabeling time, imaging slices were acquired at total delay time ( 2 ) by using echo planar imaging (EPI) as the readout. All saturation modules consisted of a 90-degree RF pulse followed by a spoiling gradient. The total duration of one saturation module was about 11 ms. Depending on the thickness of the saturation slab, an appropriate RF saturation pulse was automatically selected from a set of sinc RF pulses optimized for various thicknesses.",
